<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,153,251]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,153,179]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Etymology.</emphasis>
The Latin name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jordal and Smith" authorityYear="2020" box="[521,611,154,179]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Scolytodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="criniger">
<emphasis box="[521,611,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">criniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a masculine nominative adjective, meaning long-haired, referring to the very long interstrial setae on the elytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
